modules.description: This module provides a function to execute AWS API requests asynchronously using Lwt, handling authentication and region configuration. It works with AWS service calls represented as `('input, 'output, 'error) Aws.call` values, along with standard AWS credentials and region strings. A typical use case involves sending signed HTTP requests to AWS services like S3 or DynamoDB and receiving parsed responses or error details.

This module executes AWS API requests asynchronously using Lwt, handling authentication and region configuration. It operates on AWS service calls represented as `('input, 'output, 'error) Aws.call`, along with credentials and region strings. It is used to send signed HTTP requests to services like S3 or DynamoDB and receive parsed responses or error details.
